ms_sudo - sudo(8) command wrapper for more spiritual engineering

ABOUT

  ms_sudo is a wrapper command for sudo(8).
  When 仏滅 (Butsumetsu), the worst day in 六曜 (Rokuyou),
  this command warns and lets the user tell ありがとう to Server.
  (you must type "Server" with the capital letter.)

INSTLATION

1. get qreki.pl (written by H.Takano and N.Ueno) and put to perl library path.

  % wget http://www3.biwako.ne.jp/~nobuaki/qreki/qreki.pl
  % sudo mv qreki.pl /path/to/perl_libs

2. rename original sudo to sudo.orig

  % cd /usr/bin
  % sudo mv sudo sudo.orig

3. put ms_sudo to /usr/bin/sudo

  % mv ~/ms_sudo/sudo to /usr/bin/sudo

